HEADWORD: Metencephalon
<hw>Met`en*ceph"a*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Met-</ets> + <ets>encephalon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The posterior part of the brain, including the medulla; the
afterbrain. Sometimes abbreviated to <xex>meten</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metensomatosis</ent>⟦br⟧
